Both configuration files have been updated successfully:

**`ios/App/App/Info.plist`** — Added four privacy usage description keys inside the top-level `<dict>`:

| Key | Value |
|---|---|
| `NSCameraUsageDescription` | This app requires access to the camera to capture photos and videos. |
| `NSMicrophoneUsageDescription` | This app requires access to the microphone to record audio during video capture. |
| `NSPhotoLibraryUsageDescription` | This app requires access to the photo library to select and display your photos. |
| `NSPhotoLibraryAddUsageDescription` | This app requires permission to save captured photos and videos to your photo library. |

All pre-existing keys (`CFBundleIdentifier`, `CFBundleName`, `CFBundleDisplayName`, `UILaunchStoryboardName`, `UIRequiredDeviceCapabilities`, `UISupportedInterfaceOrientations`) remain intact. `plutil -lint` confirms the file is valid Apple Property List XML.

**`capacitor.config.ts`** — Added the `ios` block with `contentInset: 'always'` while preserving the existing `appId`, `appName`, and `webDir` fields:

```ts
import { CapacitorConfig } from '@capacitor/cli';

const config: CapacitorConfig = {
  appId: 'com.example.myapp',
  appName: 'My Native App',
  webDir: 'dist',
  ios: {
    contentInset: 'always',
  },
};

export default config;
```
